<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_573a6fe3-df19-46a8-aa64-6cac69db8c1f" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="VIC"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>B4D2</sptc><title id="_7104fa12-335a-45f8-802a-567cbe5c0878">General requirements</title><archive-num>2019: Vic B4.2</archive-num><subclause id="_4ffc8bd9-9f7c-46da-9d2e-3b73965110da" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_8d2735fd-84e1-4e28-8395-10f0517baea5">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Fire-fighting water services for <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/2527_1.3.0.xml#_759a8632-858b-4732-8105-c8ecb30ff64d" id="_47b4e02a-715a-460f-8423-524ca39f5f5e" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">Class 2</xref> to <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/2537_1.2.0.xml#_00b3f931-804a-4e9d-ab68-e46968a51f62" id="_b3c4a164-bc77-4e68-80af-82d744feaa78" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">Class 9</xref> buildings and structures must comply with the requirements of Part <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/30#_3c0138fa-b0ae-47d1-894d-b3c4672352eb" id="_bf06df5a-1f6c-405a-b388-51fd1cafc9ec" publishing-id="vol1" referencetype="Text" scope="external" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-part">E1</xref> of Volume One of the NCC.</p></subclause><subclause id="_1e126b6d-14f4-4cd2-92e4-38be4bf06b6a" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_e3539243-859f-450c-9565-5c6979cf83b7">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>The installation of a fire-fighting water service must be in accordance with AS/NZS 3500.1. </p></subclause><subclause id="_2b98650c-b58d-489b-bb9d-b2fbc428a512" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_e09314b5-728c-49c5-abbd-7447d7744e47">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>Fire-fighting water service work must be in accordance with—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_3884fbdc-adc1-483c-ac10-55902196ad86">AS 4118.1.1,</li><li id="_ce039dd5-b28a-4479-9988-40b702ec918a">AS 4118.1.2,</li><li id="_38dec62d-7f3b-4210-80f5-bcaa25d0cfcf">AS 4118.1.3,</li><li id="_a7128401-2426-4317-9695-0946313e013f">AS 4118.1.4,</li><li id="_75987478-696c-48c5-a61e-16d69eb1364f">AS 4118.1.5,</li><li id="_ba23a7f4-9781-47a0-9439-7576d20d5a96">AS 4118.1.6,</li><li id="_9597243c-c67b-4ae6-ba43-1bd25fbe675e">AS 4118.1.7,</li><li id="_e72d43d9-c9fc-424c-9e2d-1f8278289fb9">AS 4118.1.8,</li><li id="_8291f284-ec8e-4f0e-b774-fbf301ffa69b">AS 2941,</li><li id="_ca9ebf61-5709-4072-b26d-449ff902f1ef">AS 2118.2,</li><li id="_2d19d832-a7d4-461c-8ed3-60b71a40f6dc">AS 2118.3,</li><li id="_a04f2b85-8100-45e0-916b-66497fe0743b">AS 2118.8, and</li><li id="_53340150-6d0d-4a3a-b09b-f64ce30ef973">AS 1851.</li></ol></subclause><callout id="_9f2c1da1-5592-43eb-91d5-6f5a5f55f989"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>NCC Volume One requires the installation of fire-fighting equipment including fire hose reels, fire hydrants and automatic fire suppression systems in certain types of buildings.</p><p>The installation of fire-fighting water services in Class 1 buildings is not required by NCC Volume Two, however, where these services are installed voluntarily, they must be in accordance with Part B4.</p></callout></clause>